h Conquest. Major contributions come from the recent archaeological fieldwork of Steve Bourget, Anita Cook, and Alana Cordy-Collins, as well as from John Verano's laboratory work on skeletal material from recent excavations. Mary Frame, who is a weaver as well as a scholar, offers rich new interpretations of Paracas burial garments, and Donald Proulx presents a fresh view of the nature of Nasca warfare. Elizabeth Benson's essay provides a summary of sacrificial practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aHuman sacrificezPeru. 0aIndians of South AmericazPeruxAntiquities. 0aIndians of South AmericazPeruxRites and ceremonies. 0aSacrificezPeru. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBenson, Elizabeth P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenson, Elizabeth P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBourget, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, Anita G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, Anita G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCordy-Collins, Alana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrame, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProulx, Donald A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVerano, John W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292798212423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292798212/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK